This paper discusses the architecture of a local 5G network for industrial internet, which involves network functions and operational units. This topic falls under the category of computer networks and the sub-category of network architecture, which is covered by cs.NI. The paper also discusses simulation results for latency measurements, which involves information theory and is covered by cs.IT. The concept of micro-operators and the need for ultra-reliable communication links suggest a systems engineering perspective, which is covered by cs.SY. The paper also discusses the benefits of having uO-driven local 5G networks, which involves cybersecurity considerations and is covered by cs.CYBER. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed architecture, which involves software engineering considerations and is covered by cs.SE.
